problem:
\begin{problem*}{}{}
  The sequence $(a_1,a_2,\ldots,a_n)$ is a permutation of
  $(1,2,\ldots,n)$ where $n$ is an even natural number.

  \begin{enumerate}[(i)]
    \item Prove that there exist $a_i$, $a_j$ in the sequence
      such that $n\mid (a_i+i) - (a_j+j)$.
    \item   Will the result still be true if $n$ is odd?
  \end{enumerate}
\end{problem*}
